AppMail

A PHP library that allows interaction with an instance of AppMail hosted on Google App Engine. Designed to be used in PHP projects or as a CakePHP vendor.

SOURCE
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
http://github.com/benjaminpearson/gae-web-services


USAGE
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

CakePHP:
App::import('Vendor', 'AppMailCore', array('file' => 'appmail'.DS.'appmail.core.php'));
$AppMailCore = new AppMailCore();
$AppMailCore->send("John Recipient <john.recipient@example.com>", "John Sender <john.sender@example.com>", "Subject", "Message");


PHP:
require_once "appmail".DIRECTORY_SEPARATOR."appmail.core.php";
$AppMailCore = new AppMailCore();
$AppMailCore->send("John Recipient <john.recipient@example.com>", "John Sender <john.sender@example.com>", "Subject", "Message");


See test files for more examples.